content: /*<![CDATA[*/ $('#title').html($('meta[name=map-description]').attr('content')); /*]]>*/ SHA-256 Support Added to Suspicious Object Actions for Endpoint Security April 11, 2025—Trend Vision One Endpoint Security agents now support "Log" and "Block" actions for File SHA-256 objects within the Suspicious Object List. This enhances threat response capabilities by allowing direct action on SHA-256 hashes identified as suspicious across Windows, Mac, and Linux platforms. For more information, see Suspicious Object Management. Threat Intelligence → Suspicious Object Management © 2025 Trend Micro Incorporated. All rights reserved.Search Knowledge Base
